bHttpClientLatencyStatsInterval.name: bHttpClientLatencyStatsInterval
bHttpClientLatencyStatsInterval.description: The interval during which the measurements were accumulated. The interval index one indicates the latest interval for which statistics accumulation was completed. Older the statistics data, greater the interval index value. In a system supporting a history of n intervals with IntervalCount(1) and IntervalCount(n), the most and least recent intervals respectively, the following applies at the end of an interval: - discard the value of IntervalCount(n) - the value of IntervalCount(i) becomes that of IntervalCount(i+1) for 1 <= i < n - the value of IntervalCount(1) becomes that of CurrentCount.
